{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"PASS 1 review (G6 — approach soundness): The chosen mechanism (reconstruct coverage['metrics'] from the workflow run's recorder step timings, partitioned into a DET tier (precheck) and an LLM tier (agent/batch steps), with llm_calls as a coverage-derived cost proxy) is sound and codebase-aligned — the recorder already times every step, so this avoids re-introducing the bespoke producer B-RETIRE retired. AFFIRMED: mechanism-correctness, fitness-for-purpose, and approach-selection all PASS; an alternative of re-instrumenting each pass inside the orchestrator is structurally different but strictly worse (larger blast radius, reintroduces retired bespoke timing) so the plan's approach is defensible. One coaching finding below on positive rationale.\n\n- [ ] State a POSITIVE rationale in the plan for deriving metrics from the recorder step timings rather than re-instrumenting the passes (G6 §4): the Context explains why the regression matters but not why this mechanism is the right one. (location: Context / AC1)"},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782545896295897001,"uuid":"8593a9f6-6dd3-4a46-a23b-7c76f1877436"}